      "conversationSummary": "### **Research Feedback Summary**\n\n**Advisor’s Feedback & Critique:**\n*   **Scope Concerns:** The current proposal is \"far too broad.\" The advisor explicitly discouraged a \"universal\" system approach, noting that such projects are rarely successful due to the inability to conduct rigorous evaluation.\n*   **Clarification Needed:** The advisor flagged the term \"multimodal\" as vague and underdeveloped in the draft, specifically questioning whether the student intended to utilize visual data (figures) or merely rely on metadata.\n\n**Key Recommendations & Action Items:**\n*   **Narrow the Scope:** The student must pivot from a universal system to a specific, constrained domain.\n*   **Target High-Need Areas:** The advisor suggested focusing on domains where low-resource data creates a significant bottleneck, such as rare diseases in Biomedicine or specialized topics in Material Science.\n*   **Define Modality:** The student is tasked with clearly defining and justifying the \"multimodal\" features being integrated into the system.\n\n**Decisions & Agreed Direction:**\n*   **Domain Selection:** The student has agreed to pivot the research focus to the **Biomedical domain**.\n*   **Technical Refinement:** The student has committed to clarifying the multimodal component, specifically defining the use of **chemical structure diagrams** as a distinct modality to support entity linking.\n\n**Priority/Urgency:**\n*   **High Priority:** The immediate re-scoping of the project is essential before the student can proceed with a viable research design or evaluation plan."
